document_data.Usages:
[[File:Tinplate.png|thumb|''A piece of tinplate.'']]
* Tin was commonly alloyed with [[copper]] to make [[bronze]],{{Cite dragon/148/Always Wear Your Best Suit|17}}{{Cite web/theedverse/2021-03-29 - Bloodstone Trade Bar & Halduthra}}
* Small, cheap items were made of tin, such as [[plate]]s, [[bucket]]s, [[cup]]s, [[candle]]-holders,{{Cite digital book/Shadow's Witness|?|8}} [[tankard]]s, and [[lantern]]s.
* Tinplate was a form of weather-resistant [[steel]] that was coated in a thin layer of tin dissolved in [[oil of vitriol]].
* Tin [[tuning fork]]s could be used to access the [[Elemental Plane of Air]], and the [[Quasi-Elemental Plane of Lightning|Quasi-Elemental Planes of Lightning]] and [[Quasi-Elemental Plane of Vacuum|Vacuum]].{{Cite dragon/120/Plane Speaking}}
* [[Tin golem]]s were a lesser form of [[golem]].{{Cite dragon/341/Lesser Golems|43}} [[Metagolem]]s could also be made of tin, but weren't especially effective.{{Cite dragon/159/The Dragon's Bestiary: The call of the wildspace|35}}
* [[Gondar]] priests were fond of collecting little bits of material that might come in handy, such as tin.
* [[Sembia]]n governmental officials carried or wore licenses to prove their authority, usually made of tin but occasionally [[zinc]] or [[electrum]].{{Cite web/Realmslore/Melvos Hammerstars, Part Seven}}
